# MCP Server Ecosystem

**User rule (global):** `%USERPROFILE%\.cursor\rules\mcp-server-ecosystem.mdc` — applies across all repos that use custom MCP servers.

> **Canonical source (Dedge):** `C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\.cursor\rules\mcp-server-ecosystem.mdc`

All custom MCP servers are set up from `<git-root>\DevTools\CodingTools\McpServers\Setup-<Role><Client>` folders. Each folder contains `Setup-*.ps1`, `Test-*.ps1`, and `Uninstall-*.ps1` scripts following the `<Action>-<Role><Client>` naming standard.

## Quick Setup (All Servers at Once)

```powershell
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "<git-root>\DevTools\CodingTools\McpServers\Setup-AllMcpServers\Setup-AllMcpServers.ps1"
```

> **Canonical path (Dedge):** `C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\CodingTools\McpServers\Setup-AllMcpServers\Setup-AllMcpServers.ps1`

This auto-detects whether Cursor and/or Ollama is installed and runs all relevant setup and test scripts. Use `-SkipTest` to skip verification or `-SkipSetup` to only run tests.

## Quick Test (All Servers at Once)

```powershell
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "<git-root>\DevTools\CodingTools\McpServers\Setup-AllMcpServers\Test-AllMcpServers.ps1"
```

Pre-flight checks + individual tests + summary table.

## Cursor MCP Servers

| MCP Name | Cursor Server Name | Type | Setup Folder | Key Tool |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `db2-docs` | `user-db2-docs` | Python stdio proxy | `Setup-RagMcpCursor` | `query_docs` |
| `visual-cobol-docs` | `user-visual-cobol-docs` | Python stdio proxy | `Setup-RagMcpCursor` | `query_docs` |
