## Architecture

```
Developer Machine                          <app-server>
+--------------------+                     +--------------------+
| Cursor IDE         |                     | Python HTTP RAGs   |
|  RAG proxies ------+-- HTTP :8484-8486 ->|  db2-docs          |
|  (Python stdio)    |                     |  visual-cobol-docs |
|                    |                     |  Dedge-code       |
|  db2-query --------+-- HTTP :80 -------->|  IIS: CursorDb2McpServer |
|  (Streamable HTTP) |                     |                    |
|  autodoc-query ----+-- HTTP :80 -------->|  IIS: AutoDocJson  |
|  (Streamable HTTP) |                     +--------------------+
|                    |
|  postgresql-query  |  (runs locally as Node.js stdio process)
|  (Node.js stdio)   |
+--------------------+
```

> **FK app server:** `dedge-server`

**Remote servers (on app server):**
- RAG services: Python HTTP on ports 8484-8486, unauthenticated
- DB2 query: ASP.NET Core on IIS port 80 at `/CursorDb2McpServer/`
- AutoDoc query: ASP.NET Core on IIS port 80 at `/AutoDocJson/`

**Local (on developer machine):**
- PostgreSQL query: Node.js stdio process using `postgresql-mcp-server.mjs`
- RAG stdio proxies: Python venv in `~/.cursor/rag-proxy/` forwarding to remote HTTP

## Per-Server Setup Scripts

All scripts are under `<git-root>\DevTools\CodingTools\McpServers\`:

| Action | RAG (3 servers) | DB2 Query | PostgreSQL Query | AutoDoc Query |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Setup | `Setup-RagMcpCursor\Setup-RagMcpCursor.ps1` | `Setup-Db2QueryMcpCursor\Setup-Db2QueryMcpCursor.ps1` | `Setup-PostgreSqlMcpCursor\Setup-PostgreSqlMcpCursor.ps1` | `Setup-AutoDocMcpCursor\Setup-AutoDocMcpCursor.ps1` |
| Test | `Setup-RagMcpCursor\Test-RagMcpCursor.ps1` | `Setup-Db2QueryMcpCursor\Test-Db2QueryMcpCursor.ps1` | `Setup-PostgreSqlMcpCursor\Test-PostgreSqlMcpCursor.ps1` | `Setup-AutoDocMcpCursor\Test-AutoDocMcpCursor.ps1` |
| Uninstall | `Setup-RagMcpCursor\Uninstall-RagMcpCursor.ps1` | `Setup-Db2QueryMcpCursor\Uninstall-Db2QueryMcpCursor.ps1` | `Setup-PostgreSqlMcpCursor\Uninstall-PostgreSqlMcpCursor.ps1` | `Setup-AutoDocMcpCursor\Uninstall-AutoDocMcpCursor.ps1` |

All scripts write to `~/.cursor/mcp.json`. Restart Cursor after setup or uninstall.

## Naming Standard

All folders and scripts follow `<Action>-<Role><Client>`:

| Component | Description | Examples |
|---|---|---|
| Action | What the script does | `Setup`, `Test`, `Uninstall`, `Set` |
| Role | MCP function | `AutoDocMcp`, `Db2QueryMcp`, `PostgreSqlMcp`, `RagMcp`, `UserSettings` |
| Client | Consumer tool | `Cursor`, `Ollama` |

## Detailed Rules per Server

- **DB2 Query (Cursor)**: See `mcp-db2query-cursor` rule — database list, encoding, safety rules
- **PostgreSQL Query (Cursor)**: See `mcp-postgresql-cursor` rule — database list, conventions, tools
- **RAG servers (usage)**: See `mcp-rag-usage` rule — when to call which RAG, source attribution
- **RAG setup details**: See `mcp-rag-setup` rule — architecture, prerequisites, Ollama setup

## Prerequisites

- PowerShell 7+ (`pwsh.exe`)
- Python 3.11+ (for RAG stdio proxies)
- Node.js (for PostgreSQL MCP server)
- Network access to the app server hosting remote MCP services
